Pin Reference: Connectors
============================
Library: Connector.kicad_sym

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Screw_Terminal_01x02 (2-pin, at angle=0, pins face left)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
  Pin "1" local=(-5.08, 0)     -> offset (-5.08, 0)
  Pin "2" local=(-5.08, -2.54) -> offset (-5.08, +2.54)

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Screw_Terminal_01x03 (3-pin, at angle=0, pins face left)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
  Pin "1" local=(-5.08, 2.54)  -> offset (-5.08, -2.54)
  Pin "2" local=(-5.08, 0)     -> offset (-5.08, 0)
  Pin "3" local=(-5.08, -2.54) -> offset (-5.08, +2.54)

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Power symbols (GND, +3V3, +12V) - from power.kicad_sym
---------------------------------------------------------------------
  Pin "1" local=(0, 0) -> connects at the symbol's (at x y) position
  GND:  place at bottom of component pin, angle=0 (arrow points down)
  +3V3: place at top of component pin, angle=0 (arrow points up)
  +12V: place at top of component pin, angle=0 (arrow points up)
